Description: SimpleMating is a two core package for cross optimization. It estimates usefulness for a set of crosses, using additive and/or non-additive effects, allowing for multi-trait scenarios. Furthermore, it uses a mate allocation algorithm to create a mating plan aiming to maximize a target criterion (mean parental average, total genetic value, or usefulness) and constrains the next generation inbreeding levels.
